Top Maoist leader Kundan Pahan, who was facing 128 cases including the murder of senior cops, on Sunday surrendered before the police in Ranchi. Pahan was carrying a reward of ?15 lakh on his head. The Naxalites coming forward to surrender have understood "the hollowness of Maoist ideology and believe in the Constitution", said senior CRPF officer Sanjay Lathkar.